## How to update this file

You shouldn't edit STATUS.md manually unless something has gone wrong — let the slash commands do it. They will:

- `/start-next-chunk` → flip a chunk from ⬜ to 🟡, set "Active chunk" + "Last updated"
- `/finish-chunk` → flip 🟡 to 🟢, fill Completed + Commit columns, advance "Active chunk" to the next pending chunk, append any decisions/notes the session generated
- `/log-decision`, `/log-note`, `/log-issue` → append to the corresponding sections mid-session
- `/add-chunk` → insert a new chunk row + renumber subsequent rows

If you do edit manually, keep the format intact — the slash commands parse the table.
